==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Probator
<hw>Pro*ba"tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>An examiner; an approver.</def>
<rj><au>Maydman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(O. Eng. Law)</fld> <def>One who, when indicted for
crime, confessed it, and accused others, his accomplices, in order to
obtain pardon; a state's evidence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Probatory</ent>⟦br⟧
